sd=Transaction Authorization	This service domain handles risk based authorization for interactive customer transactions. This combines the context (channel) transaction, customer details and recent activity analysis as appropriate. The authorization may require a specific level of party/customer authentication to get approval.	"A customer payment request from their current account is authorized during an assisted servicing session"	This service domain is used to mitigate transaction risk for interactive product and service access fulfillment and works in collaboration with customer identity authentication services. It analyses recent customer activity in order to detect possible out of pattern/fraudulent behavior and authorizes transactions accordingly. The authorization can be subject to obtaining increased levels of customer authentication by requiring the customer to provide additional proof of identity.
sdpath=transaction-authorization
crpath=interactive-transaction-assessment
crr=Interactive Transaction Assessment Instance
mcr=InteractiveTransactionAssessment
bqs=
CONFIG
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	evaluate	Evaluate a proposed interactive transaction for authorization		evaluateInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	update	Update details of a proposed transaction for authorization		updateInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	exchange	Verify, accept, override etc. a transaction authorization		exchangeInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	execute	Execute an automated action for transaction authorization (e.g. upload data)		executeInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	request	Request manual intervention (e.g. engage a specialist)		requestInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	grant	Obtain an authorization grant from transaction authorization		grantInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc
InteractiveTransactionAssessment	retrieve	Retrieve details about an interactive transaction authorization		retrieveInteractiveTransactionAssessment		#desc